    "The tweets were collected using keywords related to infectious diseases.",
    "All the above-mentioned datasets rely on textual content; however, there is a dataset called ArCOV19-Rumors [75], which consists of 9,414 tweets that were manually labeled as false (1,753), true (1,831), and others (5,830), which are related to 138 claims This dataset works on two levels: claim-level verification and tweet-level verification, both of which have two labels, namely, true and false.",
